decision_conditions:
The applicant is advised that Transport for London have the following further comments:
-  The outside party agrees to inform TFL Engineering if any alarms on the NR monitoring, along with the agreed action;
-  The contractor will provide copies of the Piling Method statement for review;
-  The contractor will provide a record copy of the Cat 3 Check and the relevant Form 3 Approval by NR;
-  Transport for London maintains the right to object to any design or method of work which we believe may have a detrimental impact upon TFL infrastructure or operation. Tide Construction should consult with TIP on a regular basis to determine what activities may have an impact on TFL infrastructure such that we can agree a method of working that is acceptable to both parties;
-  TFL Infrastructure Protection inspectors will monitor the works, plant and
methods of working as detailed in any agreed lifting plan or method statement, in order to ensure the protection of TfL infrastructure and operations. Reasonable facilities shall be made available to TFL Inspectors so that they can carry out their duties;
-  You are reminded that the responsibility for the health, safety and
environmental aspects of the works on site rests fully and unreservedly with you and your designated contractors. This letter of no objection to the works detailed in the documents listed above does not absolve you from that responsibility, nor does it confirm or suggest that you have met any statutory requirements;
- This notification of No Objection does not constitute acceptance of liability by TFL for any accident, incident or breach of stature that may arise from the design and method adopted for construction.
